HEADWORD: weeping love grass
<hw>weeping love grass</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a perennial South African
grass (<spn>Eragrostis curvula</spn>) having densely clumped flimsy
stems; introduced into U.S. esp. for erosion control.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> African love grass.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Weepingly</ent>⟦br⟧
